,Recommended,248390,32832669,Posted: 26 June,all,tN|Steve-nC-,"I needed to hit up the wiki to figure some things out because the in-game tutorial is sadly lacking clarity. The pressure to fight off the horde every hour is stressful, but enjoyable. It gives you something else to think about other than exploring and building. Your dwarves respawn in the event they die, so there does not seem to be much in the way of death punishment. You even get your structures back when the horde breaks through walls, so there is not a lot of negative reinforcement to get aggrivated by.It's a charming mix of terraria and minecraft that you can casually play at your own pace. I'd definitely recommend it to a friend."
