76561197962657563,Not Recommended,248390,32550845,Posted: 18 June,all,Drat,"Not a horrible game, but not what I'm looking for.  I was lured in by the tower defense tag, but this is NOT a tower defense game at all. There are a couple of useless towers but no tower defense strategy.  As the name implies, this is a crafting game.  You craft tiers of stuff that you don't need just so you can unlock more tiers of stuff that you don't need.  The monster waves grow stronger over time making this a race to gather mats and unlock crafting tiers so that you can craft stong enough armor and weapons for your dwarves to survive.  You just have to craft a million chandeliers, decorative chairs, and wall ornaments to unlock the next tier of armor.- The rushed pace prevents a casual exploration and defense building play style.- since monster portals open right next to your base, you pretty much have to accept partial base destruction and just rebuild.- The world you're on is VERY tiny,  Maybe seven screens wide and four screens deep.If the world were large, like other 2D survial games, and you were able to explore at your own pace, build a defense, and then summon monsters when ready, this would be a good game.  As a hurry up and craft a million things game, it's boring."
