76561198064373133,Recommended,248390,8279349,"Posted: 25 December, 2013",all,Ysthrall,"I can heartily reccomend this game as a bouncy and detailed building/simulation/exploration game. The pace is not very fast, but there's always something to do. This is the sort of game that you'll find yourself playing for another 5 minutes, until that is built. And that area is explored. And those are killed by your screaming little beardies. And so on, for hours... :)There's a nice variation of climatic factors that does have an impact, but not an unbalancing one on the game. The crafting and spellcasting system is intuitive and simple, as is the scaling up of equipment and weaponry. Fighting and hunting and holding off the nicely balanced waves of monsters makes for an additional dimension, although after a time it's possible to have so many traps and Tesla towers (where did they get those?) that the dwarves can just sit on the roof drinking beer while another wave of monsters dies in the traps and cages and lightning.There's quite a lot of surprises hidden around the maps, which are lush with wonderful backgrounds as well. It's a game with a massive amount of replayability, with a lot of things to poke (and some things, crawling in the depths, that don't like being poked).I look forwards to the full version of the game and the rest of the campaign."
