,Not Recommended,248390,9954675,"Posted: 27 April, 2014",all,Annasys,"I really want to like this gameThis type of game is something I enjoy. And this game looks like it will become a great game if the developers keep developing it. However, as it stands right now, it has very limited depth. The tech tree seems out of sorts. It's difficult to survive in the beginning due to being unable to build adequate shelter before the first invasion.Invasions get harder as the game progresses. That's great. Except they only get harder in so far as there are more mobs in each invasion. At some point, you will be unable to complete an invasion before daylight. I have all of my guys with maxed out weapons and high levels of experience with them. I have multiple defenseive structures. I still can't complete an invasion.There are other points of contention: Dwarf AI is lackluster at best. Minerals become very rare. Towards the end of the game, it's nigh impossible to gather enough materials to equip you dwarves, much less build grand castles under the mountains. There is no way to automate anything. This includes things like making sure tables are stocked with food. Transit AI is terrible, and in some situations is so broken that you have to manually remove them and replace them in order to get them to work properly.Perhaps in the future, this game will become a fun game to play. Until then, play the first hour or so, and then go find something better than the tedium that is Craft the World."
