,Recommended,248390,8265991,"Posted: 24 December, 2013",all,Wu Ziheng,"This is one of the best Survival/Crafting games I've ever played. For an early access this game is fully playable and incredibly enjoyable.The Gameplay: Similar to Terraria/Starbound this game has you in a 2D world mining and crafting to help your dwarven brethren survive. Unlike T/S you don't directly control each dwarf, instead you give commands ala, Dungeon Keeper, for your 'minions' to carry out. You can however 'possess' a dwarf and control him directly, if you need better control for fighting or you just want a specific task done.The Sound: The sounds are what you'd expect them to be. Trees sound like trees when you cut them down, rocks sound like rocks, etc.Overall: This is one of my most favorite games in this genre due to its colorful nature and well designed implementation.Personal Likes: Skeletons that attack your base form live ladders by holding their shields above their head for their allies to climb on often making a chain several skeletons high to breach walls. Goblins build makeshift ladders to climb and descend into your defenses.Personal Dislikes: The crafting system needs a bit of tweaking. When you pull up a recipe you still need to drag each item into its correct place to make it. It's not so bad when it's simple things like three logs, but when it's multiple items found on different tabs to make a complex recipe it can be a bit tedious to find all the pieces. Maybe there's a way to instantly place the items, but I haven't found it yet.Final Thoughts: This is a great game which I have already spent many hours with. I bought it on a whim and did not regret it. Like any Early Access game it needs a bit of polishing, but it is an enjoyable experience that you must play even if you are only slightly interested in it."
