,Recommended,248390,8229237,"Posted: 23 December, 2013",all,OmNom,"A Superb Example of 2D RPG Sandbox Survival!As the developer says, If you like games such as Terraria, Dwarf Fortress, and Dungeon Keeper, then you are going to love this game. It is very well polished even in it's early access form. It has excellent graphics, sounds, and game play.Lots of collectible resources and a simple crafting system make crafting items a breeze, and the armor and weapons for your dwarves are well balanced. You truely feel you have accomplished something when you take the time to outfit your motley crew with the latest item upgrades, allowing them to take on larger hordes of enemies, but not making them invincible.As with any game of this nature, it will likely take you a couple play throughs to get the hang of things. Challenging enough to keep you playing for hours on end, while still giving you helpful queues along the way to aid you in progressing. You never feel lost trying to figure out what you should do next, but you also never feel like the game is making decisions for you.The only issue I ran into was while trying to get my dwarves' house secure enough that they would sleep. I had built the house, and placed beds, but the game didn't seem to recognize the house was secure. (A secure home is completely sealed with or without a door, and contains a Totem and a bed for each of your dwarves). A quick internet search suggested that I exit the game and restart. After doing this, the game recognized my house was secure and I never had trouble from then on.I have played Craft the World for 10 hours so far, and have not fully explored or conquered the first small world. I am sure I will log some serious time on this game. I highly recommend this game!"
